import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='volume', bins=50, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(data['volume'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['volume'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Trading Volume')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily trading volume?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='adjclose', data=data, label='Adjusted Close')
    plt.title('What is the trend of the S&P 500 index over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Adjusted Close')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
